# A missing hashed asset must 404 — never fall through to the SPA shell below.
# Otherwise a request during a deploy propagation gap serves index.html with a
# 200, and because _headers marks /assets/* immutable-for-a-year by path, the
# edge caches that HTML under the asset URL and poisons it for a year.
/assets/*    /404.html    404

# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback — any non-asset, non-API route serves index.html
# so the Solid Router can take over and render the correct page.
# Real Functions in /functions are matched FIRST by Pages, so /api/* etc. still work.
/*    /index.html    200
